<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Aznet - About Me</title>
    <link href="/css/tailwind.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="/css/aznet-theme.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
      body {
        background: #000;
        min-height: 100vh;
        position: relative;
      }
      .about-container {
        background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
        border: 1px solid var(--color-primary);
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--color-primary);
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 3rem auto 3rem auto;
        padding: 2.5rem 2rem 2rem 2rem;
      }
      .about-title {
        font-family: 'Courier New', 'Lucida Console', monospace;
        color: var(--color-primary);
        font-size: 2.4rem;
        font-weight: 900;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--color-primary);
      }
      .about-section-title {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--color-primary);
      }
      .about-desc {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        text-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--color-primary);
      }
      .about-back {
        display: inline-block;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        background: var(--color-primary);
        color: var(--color-body-dark);
        font-weight: 700;
        padding: 0.5rem 1.5rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--color-primary);
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: var(--transition);
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--color-primary);
      }
      .about-back:hover {
        background: var(--color-secondary);
        color: var(--color-body-dark);
        box-shadow: 0 0 15px var(--color-secondary);
      }
      .about-list {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
        text-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--color-primary);
      }
      .about-list li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }
      .about-contact {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        text-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--color-primary);
        border: 1px solid var(--color-primary);
        padding: 1rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--color-primary);
      }
      .about-contact a {
        color: var(--color-secondary);
        text-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--color-secondary);
      }
      .about-contact a:hover {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--color-primary);
      }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="mbr-scanlines"></div>
    <div class="mbr-scanline"></div>
    <div class="mbr-flicker"></div>

    <%- include('partials/header', { currentPage: 'about' }) %>

    <main class="about-container">
        <a href="/" class="about-back">← Back to Projects</a>
        <div class="about-title">About Hugo Villeneuve</div>
        <div class="about-desc">
            I build tools that solve real problems, not just pretty interfaces. My projects come from actual pain points I've experienced in gaming and development. If you're looking for another to-do app or weather widget, you're in the wrong place.
        </div>

        <div class="about-section-title">Background</div>
        <div class="about-desc">
            I've been building things since I was old enough to break them. My approach is simple: if something's annoying me, I'll build a tool to fix it. That's how most of my projects start - from real problems that need real solutions.
        </div>

        <div class="about-section-title">Skills</div>
        <ul class="about-list">
            <li>IT Infrastructure - Because someone has to keep the lights on</li>
            <li>Problem Solving - I break things, then I fix them (usually)</li>
            <li>Automation - If I have to do it more than once, I'll write a script</li>
            <li>Gaming - I play games so you don't have to build the same tools I do</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="about-section-title">Languages</div>
        <ul class="about-list">
            <li>JavaScript/TypeScript - For when I need to build something quickly</li>
            <li>Python - For when I need to process data or automate something</li>
            <li>Bash - For when I need to make the computer do my bidding</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="about-section-title">Why Aznet?</div>
        <div class="about-desc">
            I build tools I actually use. If I'm not using it, I'm not building it. That means you get tools that solve real problems, not just pretty interfaces. And no, I won't build you a to-do app.
        </div>

        <div class="about-contact">
            <p>Want to work together? <a href="mailto:aznettechnicalservices@gmail.com">Email me</a> or find me on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/hugo-villeneuve-aznet">LinkedIn</a>.</p>
        </div>
    </main>

    <footer class="mt-16 relative z-10" style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto 2rem auto; border: 1px solid var(--color-primary); box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--color-primary);">
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
            <p class="text-center font-medium" style="color: var(--color-primary); text-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--color-primary);">© <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> Aznet - All rights reserved</p>
        </div>
    </footer>
</body>
</html> 